Day 39 — Lasso Regression

📌 Overview

On Day 39, I learned Lasso Regression, a Regularization technique (L1) used to reduce overfitting and perform feature selection.

🧠 What is Lasso Regression?

Lasso Regression adds L1 penalty to the cost function, which can shrink some coefficients to zero.

📈 Formula

Loss = RSS + \lambda \sum |w|

λ (Lambda) → Regularization parameter

Shrinks coefficients

Removes less important features


💡 Key Takeaway

Lasso Regression helps in reducing overfitting and automatic feature selection.

